1)Entries for the Monthly Scenario Contest must be turned in by a week 
from Saturday.  Please upload them as a zip file just so we don't have 
accidently overwrite of somebody else's entry and make sure to include 
 some way to identify who created the scenario.  If you can't access 
the group files section, email the entry to me.  Also, using scenario 
numbers from the tevfifty or my set is a very *BAD* idea.  I would 
suggest using #s from 220 to 240 as your entries.

2)Next week, we are taking nominations for themes for 2nd Monthly 
Scenario Contest.
